    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Stephen D. Crocker</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:SteveCrockerJI1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/SteveCrockerJI1.jpg/330px-SteveCrockerJI1.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"202\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/SteveCrockerJI1.jpg/500px-SteveCrockerJI1.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/SteveCrockerJI1.jpg/960px-SteveCrockerJI1.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:SteveCrockerJI1.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Steve Crocker <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Stephen David (Steve) Crocker</b>, (born October 15, 1944)<br />\nan American computer scientist, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet\">internet</a> pioneer, and inventor of the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Request_for_Comments\">Request for Comments</a> (RFC) series \n<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.\nHe holds a B.Sc. and Ph.D from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_California,_Los_Angeles\">University of California, Los Angeles</a> in 1968 and 1977 respectively.\nHe was part of the team that developed the protocols for the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ARPANET\">ARPANET</a> which were the foundation for today's internet.\nEarlier in the 60s, he was affiliated with <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">MIT</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, \nand worked with <a href=\"/Richard_Greenblatt\" title=\"Richard Greenblatt\">Richard Greenblatt</a> and <a href=\"/Donald_Eastlake\" title=\"Donald Eastlake\">Donald Eastlake</a> on <a href=\"/Mac_Hack\" title=\"Mac Hack\">The Greenblatt Chess Program</a> or <i>Mac Hack VI</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1967_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1967 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stephen_D._Crocker&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1967_...\">1967 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stephen_D._Crocker&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1967 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Richard_Greenblatt\" title=\"Richard Greenblatt\">Richard Greenblatt</a>, <a href=\"/Donald_Eastlake\" title=\"Donald Eastlake\">Donald Eastlake</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stephen D. Crocker</a> (<b>1967</b>). <i>The Greenblatt Chess Program</i>. Proceedings of the AfiPs Fall Joint Computer Conference, Vol. 31, reprinted (<b>1988</b>) in <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Compendium\" title=\"Computer Chess Compendium\">Computer Chess Compendium</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.computerhistory.org/projects/chess/related_materials/text/2-4.Greenblatt_Chess_Program/The_Greenblatt_Chess_Program.Greenblatt_Eastlake_Crocker.1967.Fall_Joint_Computer_Conference.062303060.sm.pdf\">pdf</a> from <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a> or as <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/6176\">pdf or ps</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://libraries.mit.edu/dspace-mit/\">DSpace</a> at <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">MIT</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a> (<b>1969</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1\">Host Software</a></i>. RFC 1</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a> (<b>1969</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3\">Documentation conventions</a></i>. RFC 3</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/1014198.804309\">Design considerations for a QM-1 based multimicroprocessor emulation system</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/micro/micro1978.html#Crocker78\">MICRO 1978</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Donald_Eastlake\" title=\"Donald Eastlake\">Donald Eastlake</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://jis.qyv.name/\">Jeffrey I. Schiller</a> (<b>1994</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1750\">Randomness Recommendations for Security</a></i>. RFC 1750</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stephen_D._Crocker&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Donald_Eastlake\" title=\"Donald Eastlake\">Donald Eastlake</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://jis.qyv.name/\">Jeffrey I. Schiller</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc4086\">Randomness Requirements for Security</a></i>. RFC 4086</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pid/209/5887.html\">Howard Eland</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pid/91/4441.html\">Russ Mundy</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pid/91/4441.html\">Suresh Krishnaswamy</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc4986\">Requirements Related to DNS Security (DNSSEC) Trust Anchor Rollover</a></i>. RFC 4986</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pid/45/3615.html\">Alexander McKenzie</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a> (<b>2012</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6529\">Host/Host Protocol for the ARPA Network</a></i>. RFC 6529</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steve Crocker</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pid/13/4027.html\">Scott Rose</a> (<b>2013</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6975\">Signaling Cryptographic Algorithm Understanding in DNS Security Extensions (DNSSEC)</a></i>. RFC 6975</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stephen_D._Crocker&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Crocker\">Steve Crocker from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.internethalloffame.org/inductees/steve-crocker\">Steve Crocker | Internet Hall of Fame</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.internethalloffame.org//blog/2012/05/18/meet-man-who-invented-instructions-internet\">Meet the Man Who Invented the Instructions for the Internet | Internet Hall of Fame</a>, May 18, 2012</li>\n<li> Steve Crocker - <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Hall_of_Fame\">Internet Hall of Fame</a> Pioneer, May, 2012, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YouTube\">YouTube</a> Video</li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/ErOvs-uRC0Y?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://labs.ripe.net/history-of-networking/the-rfc-series-steve-crocker\">The RFC Series: Steve Crocker — RIPE Labs</a>, December 2019 </li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stephen_D._Crocker&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Crocker\">Steve Crocker from Wikipedia</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Steve_Crocker\">Category:Steve Crocker - Wikimedia Commons</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/RFC-Editor\">H. Flanagan</a> (ed.) (<b>2019</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8700.html\">RFC 8700: Fifty Years of RFCs</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.computerhistory.org/resources/text/Oral_History/Greenblatt_Richard/greenblatt.oral_history_transcript.2005.102657935.pdf\">Oral History of Richard Greenblatt</a> (pdf) from <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Richard_Greenblatt\" title=\"Richard Greenblatt\">Richard Greenblatt</a>, <a href=\"/Donald_Eastlake\" title=\"Donald Eastlake\">Donald Eastlake</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Stephen D. Crocker</a> (<b>1967</b>). <i>The Greenblatt Chess Program</i>. Proceedings of the AfiPs Fall Joint Computer Conference, reprinted (<b>1988</b>) in <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Compendium\" title=\"Computer Chess Compendium\">Computer Chess Compendium</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pid/49/6744.html\">dblp: Steve Crocker</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301152319\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.070 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.610 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 98/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 234/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 26/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:7385-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301152318 and revision id 20860\n -->\n"
